	     Durban – A 43-year-old woman has been arrested after a newborn baby was found dumped at an informal settlement near KwaMashu hostel on Wednesday. A resident, who asked not to be named, told News24 that she had seen the woman near a local public toilet on Tuesday afternoon. ALSO READ: Teen girl allegedly dumped baby son into pit toilet in Limpopo "She was in labour pain as she was heavily pregnant at the time. We confronted her with other residents when the foetus was found this morning (Wednesday). "She failed to explain where she was keeping her baby as it was clear to everyone that she was no longer pregnant. We then decided to call police," said the resident. ALSO READ: Woman allegedly dumps newborn down concrete pit toilet Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele confirmed the arrest of the woman. "A foetus was found dumped near the informal dwellings by the railway station at the hostel at about 07:45. KwaMashu police arrested the woman and she will be charged for concealment of birth," she said.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  